metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #873
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: FxPlanet #554
metadata.description:
🟢〰Storyline〰🟢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔴〰Rarity〰🔴

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
◼ The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
◼ For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
◼ Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔵〰Social〰🔵

◼ Participant in events or get achievements to win some prizes.
So it's significant to see you on the discord server. Checkout rarity table, achievements rewards, … on the webpage.
📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🟠〰Interact〰🟠

◼ You can rotate around of planets by “WASD” keys on the keyboard or arrow keys.
◼ Zoom In by “E” key and Zoom Out by “Q”.
◼ Full HD texture by Key “1”.
◼ 4k texture by Key “2”.
◼ 8k texture by Key “3”.

metadata.name: The Climb #1
metadata.description:
The climb is about the search for purpose.

Everyone needs a purpose, a path that leads somewhere. Whether you reach it or not is not the point, it’s about the climb. The search for a purpose gives our life meaning. It gives us a reason to look for something more.

Unfortunately, there is no universal truth as to what your purpose in life is. Everyone is unique. Different. We are the product of our upbringing, environment and the cumulative sum of thousands of microdecisions. We need to find meaning for ourselves. Our unique meaning. On this path, we climb alone.

“The Climb” is created to be raw, unique, beautiful and violently volatile, much like our lives.


Everything is written in javascript and p5js.
It can sometimes take a little while to render on older computers.

metadata.name: Skyward Theatre #2
metadata.description:
“So the sky became the most enchanting canvas of all, limitless in its potential. What was painted there would be beautiful, if only for a moment”

---

Gen art relies on the randomness of the universe to fill artistic systems with life. So it is with a fireworks display. There is a plan, arrangement, and sequence. But the system only comes alive when it leaves the realm of order and control. Skyward Theatre is a tribute to this analog generative technique.

---
- Made with p5js
- Press p to pause
- Press s to save png

metadata.name: WTW 2001-2022 #35
metadata.description:
---------------------------------------------------------------------
From the pixel-lab vault - original version released in February 2001
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image - with finer details

Right-click: Save/Copy the image

A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine 
written in vanilla JavaScript
some more info in the source-code
The work will refresh and restart after some time
-------------------------------------------------


I put this work online back in February 2001, 
as a java-applet; not working in most browsers any more. '__'

Rewrote it today; slightly adjusted for fxhash; 
since it was an interactive-animated lower-res work.
Although most of that fine-tuning I did back then.

You can find the original wtw at: 
https://elout.home.xs4all.nl/index2001.html
(more an archive of web-works and experiments between 1998-2007)


xxx Amsterdam chillout

For the love of Art, a High-5, and tons of pixels ^__^

August 20 2022

metadata.name: Tangled #33
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #276
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan
